Synopsis:
   set status_mode [<text>]

Description:
   This variable sets the string displayed in the status bar when the
   current channel has at least one mode set (not including +o or +v).
   If no modes are set, nothing is displayed.

   This string is represented as %+ in the STATUS_FORMAT string.  When
   used inside STATUS_MODE, it will expand to the actual modes and their
   arguments.

Examples:
   Customizing the appearance of the channel modes in the status bar:
      /set status_mode Mode %+

See Also:
   mode(1); set(4) status_format

